contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:05.932 --> 01:09.573
I want you on message, and
the message is Leslie Knope.

01:09.636 --> 01:10.944
If you're not
talking about you,

01:11.004 --> 01:12.244
you're talking
about the wrong thing.

01:12.305 --> 01:13.807
I hate talking about myself.

01:13.873 --> 01:17.343
Get over it. I talk about myself constantly.
Everyone loves me for it.

01:17.410 --> 01:19.321
I really am amazing.

01:19.379 --> 01:21.290
When you work in government,
people often suspect

01:21.347 --> 01:22.382
that you're anti-business.

01:22.449 --> 01:24.827
So I'm throwing a little meet
and greet with business owners,

01:24.884 --> 01:26.488
and I've asked
Tom's company to help.

01:26.553 --> 01:29.227
Here's my opening line.
Hi. I'm Leslie Knope,

01:29.289 --> 01:31.701
and I'm in the business
of being City Councilor.

01:31.758 --> 01:33.362
Oh, my God.
I'm not going to use that.

01:33.426 --> 01:35.804
This is your primary target.

01:35.862 --> 01:37.773
President of the Chamber of
Commerce, Martin Kernston.

01:37.831 --> 01:42.246
Oh, yes. From Kernston Rubber Nipples.
The Nipple King.

01:43.269 --> 01:47.012
Photos, bios, likes, dislikes,
prescription medications.

01:47.073 --> 01:49.451
I've heard of Martin Kernston.
I know a little bit about him.

01:49.509 --> 01:51.819
Oh, really? Well, which of his
advisors does he trust more,

01:51.878 --> 01:53.221
Ted Flirtman or Rex Baggs?

01:53.279 --> 01:55.225
Well, it depends. Flirtman
is more of a confidant.

01:55.281 --> 01:56.919
I made up both those names.

01:56.983 --> 01:58.291
Okay, I'm on it.

02:00.053 --> 02:01.191
Get at me.

02:01.254 --> 02:03.393
Jean-Ralphio, stop crying.

02:03.456 --> 02:06.835
What? Hold on.
Slow down. Hold on.

02:07.994 --> 02:11.669
Allergic to chestnuts and...

02:12.499 --> 02:14.376
Good haircuts.

02:21.875 --> 02:24.879
It's too tight. Looser. I
feel like we need to inflate it more.

02:24.944 --> 02:27.925
No, I told you. I'm a sumo
wrestler after he lost the weight.

02:27.981 --> 02:29.551
I take it
we're having a party.

02:29.983 --> 02:33.396
Dude, I knew there was something
I forgot to tell you. Sorry.

02:33.453 --> 02:34.488
No, no, no. It's fine.

02:34.554 --> 02:36.932
Why should you guys tell me you
were gonna have an enormous party?

02:36.990 --> 02:39.470
I didn't tell you I was gonna
be quietly working in my room.

02:39.526 --> 02:40.834
- That's a good point.
- Yeah, yeah.

02:40.894 --> 02:42.066
I guess we're even.

02:42.128 --> 02:43.801
If you need me,
I'll definitely be awake,

02:43.863 --> 02:47.709
because I won't be able to
sleep because of the party.

02:47.934 --> 02:49.607
You know? So...

02:51.404 --> 02:52.576
All right.

02:52.639 --> 02:54.915
My family is very
non-confrontational.

02:54.974 --> 02:56.885
My parents' method
of problem solving is

02:56.943 --> 02:58.752
to kind of keep
everything bottled up

02:58.811 --> 03:02.088
and just subtly hint
at what's bothering them.

03:02.148 --> 03:06.255
And after 36 years,
they are still divorced.

03:08.254 --> 03:09.562
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

03:09.622 --> 03:11.693
Tom, this is not
what I pictured at all.

03:11.758 --> 03:14.500
This looks like a party
for Entertainment 720.

03:14.561 --> 03:17.041
Is Entertainment 720
running for office?

03:17.096 --> 03:18.598
It's a small business.

03:18.665 --> 03:19.666
You're trying to
show people you have

03:19.732 --> 03:21.837
a good relationship
with small businesses.

03:21.901 --> 03:23.744
Now the party?
That's all about you, boo.

03:23.803 --> 03:25.942
Okay. Then shouldn't my face
be on these rugs?

03:26.005 --> 03:27.484
I'm sorry, no.

03:27.540 --> 03:30.111
It's always been a dream of mine to
be a rug, and it's finally happened.

03:30.176 --> 03:31.519
Tom, now is not
the time for you

03:31.578 --> 03:33.421
to explore your
weird dreams, okay?

03:33.479 --> 03:35.891
I want all of this gone.
All of it.

03:35.949 --> 03:39.328
Except that cake. Keep that cake here.
Just scrape off the words.

03:44.457 --> 03:49.634
Donna? Blue shirt,
badge, night stick.

03:50.029 --> 03:52.339
You are a policewoman.

03:52.398 --> 03:53.843
Yep. You're a regular...

03:53.900 --> 03:57.313
Sherlock Holmes. I solved
that mystery before you did.

03:57.370 --> 03:59.247
Okay, this was fun.

04:00.073 --> 04:04.283
Andy, you are U.F.C. legend, Chuck Liddell.
That's right.

04:05.078 --> 04:06.386
Girl from The Ring.

04:06.446 --> 04:08.756
To me, Sherlock
Holmes is literally

04:08.815 --> 04:11.352
the greatest character
in the Western canon.

04:11.417 --> 04:14.057
Smart, intuitive, handsome.

04:14.120 --> 04:15.929
Replace his pasty
British frailty

04:15.989 --> 04:18.993
with superhuman physical
fitness, and you get...

04:19.058 --> 04:21.038
Sherlock Traeger.

04:21.094 --> 04:23.973
Mr. Potato Head.
That's right.

04:24.030 --> 04:26.738
Hey, where's my lovely daughter tonight?
She's at home.

04:26.799 --> 04:27.800
I knew that
you would be here,

04:27.867 --> 04:29.312
and I was worried
that you might be

04:29.369 --> 04:31.042
concerned seeing us
together at night.

04:31.104 --> 04:32.105
You're a very
thoughtful guy,

04:32.171 --> 04:33.548
but really,
I have no problem

04:33.606 --> 04:35.279
with the two of you
dating, really.

04:35.341 --> 04:38.254
I mean, look at you. You're
just, you know, beautiful.

04:38.311 --> 04:41.349
You're beautiful. On the inside
where your spirit lives.

04:41.414 --> 04:43.860
Listen. Tell her, "Come to the
party," and I don't mind at all.

04:43.916 --> 04:46.021
Oh, good. I'll text her.

04:48.321 --> 04:50.198
Okay. You can text
without looking at your phone?

04:50.256 --> 04:51.894
I think it's rude
not to maintain eye contact

04:51.958 --> 04:55.303
with the people that I'm talking to.

04:55.361 --> 04:56.396
That's from me.

04:56.462 --> 04:59.443
Wow! That's amazing!

04:59.499 --> 05:01.172
High five.
Wow.

05:04.103 --> 05:06.879
Hey. Ron. Good to see you.

05:06.939 --> 05:08.612
Weren't you
a pirate last year?

05:08.675 --> 05:11.622
Yes. This is my
Halloween costume.

05:11.678 --> 05:15.353
Andrew, are you aware that your
bathroom faucet is leaking?

05:15.415 --> 05:18.953
Are you kidding me? I just
stuffed a sock in it yesterday.

05:19.018 --> 05:20.554
What else
do they want me to do?

05:20.620 --> 05:23.624
There's an exposed wire
above the bathtub as well.

05:23.690 --> 05:25.931
Oh, yeah. Shock wire.

05:25.992 --> 05:30.338
I call it that, 'cause if you take
a shower, and you touch the wire,

05:30.396 --> 05:31.932
YOU die!

05:32.398 --> 05:34.344
Yes, that is accurate.

05:34.400 --> 05:36.346
Do you have a tool box?
Yeah.

05:36.636 --> 05:40.106
No home is complete
without a proper toolbox.

05:40.173 --> 05:42.016
Here's April and Andy's.

05:42.508 --> 05:46.115
A hammer, half of a pretzel,

05:46.179 --> 05:51.458
baseball card, some cartridge
that says Sonic and Hedgehog,

05:51.517 --> 05:53.997
a scissor half,
and a flashlight.

05:55.421 --> 05:57.492
Filled with jelly beans.

06:01.961 --> 06:04.237
Although I have not worked
with you professionally,

06:04.297 --> 06:05.674
as a private citizen,

06:05.732 --> 06:07.473
I have personally patronized

06:07.533 --> 06:09.638
each and every one
of your establishments.

06:09.702 --> 06:12.273
I've never seen you buy a
salad at Sue's Salads.

06:12.338 --> 06:13.874
That's because
I don't hate myself, Tania.

06:14.774 --> 06:17.482
I'm sorry. I know I should
be chasing your vote,

06:17.543 --> 06:18.988
but I stand
behind my decision

06:19.045 --> 06:21.116
to avoid salad
and other disgusting things.

06:21.180 --> 06:24.184
And I think I have a lot of support
in the community for that.

06:24.250 --> 06:27.254
Despite the fact that this seems
like a party for Tom's face,

06:27.320 --> 06:29.027
uh, I think
it's going pretty well.

06:29.088 --> 06:32.331
When in doubt,
in Pawnee, slam salad.

06:32.392 --> 06:34.895
I'm just especially thankful that
you could come, Mr. President.

06:34.961 --> 06:36.440
Martin.
Martin.

06:36.496 --> 06:38.476
You were responsible for
the Harvest Festival, right?

06:38.531 --> 06:41.808
No. Yes. Well, it was a team effort.
I barely did anything.

06:41.868 --> 06:44.747
I held them back, actually.
They succeeded despite me.

06:46.672 --> 06:49.653
I'm sorry. I worked very hard
on that event. I'm just...

06:49.709 --> 06:53.054
Bureaucrats aren't used to bragging
about themselves.

06:53.112 --> 06:55.388
Tom, come over here and
talk about how great I am.

06:55.448 --> 06:58.156
Martin! Tom Haverford
I threw this shindig.

06:58.217 --> 07:01.164
Yes. Tom, tell Martin how hard I
worked on the Harvest Festival.

07:01.220 --> 07:03.063
It was incredible.

07:03.122 --> 07:04.863
A lot of people say
the Harvest Festival

07:04.924 --> 07:06.631
is what launched
Entertainment 720.

07:06.692 --> 07:08.035
No one says that.
I just said it.

07:08.094 --> 07:10.165
My company,
Entertainment 720,

07:10.229 --> 07:13.005
has an amazing business
opportunity for Kernston's.

07:13.065 --> 07:16.137
Mind if I steal you away a few
seconds, give you the 'tails?

07:16.202 --> 07:18.148
The 'tails?
The details.

07:18.204 --> 07:21.276
Most people would probably say
the deets I say the 'tails.

07:21.340 --> 07:22.944
Just one example
of innovation.

07:23.009 --> 07:28.015
Look, I don't like to throw around
the word butt-head too often.

07:28.080 --> 07:29.354
If you call
everybody a butt-head,

07:29.415 --> 07:30.826
then it kind of
loses its impact.

07:30.883 --> 07:33.090
But I can say
without hesitation

07:33.152 --> 07:35.496
that Tom is
being a real dick.

07:37.190 --> 07:40.694
Hey. You stole the Nipple King.
Thanks a lot, traitor.

07:40.760 --> 07:42.535
I'm sorry. I just needed to
ask him about this one thing.

07:42.595 --> 07:44.939
But we're all good now. What if I
just introduce you for your speech?

07:44.997 --> 07:46.943
I have a better idea. Why don't
you go over to one of your rugs

07:46.999 --> 07:50.242
and sit on your own face? I
don't need your help anymore.

07:52.738 --> 07:55.116
Hi, there. ls there a
project you're working on?

07:55.174 --> 07:57.620
I know more than you.
All right.

07:58.845 --> 08:00.518
When April
and Andy married,

08:00.580 --> 08:02.526
I didn't get them
a wedding present.

08:02.582 --> 08:04.823
In my experience, wedding
presents are nothing more

08:04.884 --> 08:07.660
than kindling on
the divorce bonfire.

08:07.720 --> 08:11.463
But I think I found a way I can
really help them make a home.

08:13.659 --> 08:16.037
You, bean bag,
come with me.

08:16.095 --> 08:17.403
I'm an eggplant.

08:17.463 --> 08:19.568
I don't care. Come with me. Why?

08:19.632 --> 08:20.872
I need small hands.

08:22.969 --> 08:25.176
I'm scared.

08:27.173 --> 08:31.679
Look who decided to join the party.
Bro, that's awesome!

08:31.744 --> 08:33.052
Where's your costume?

08:33.111 --> 08:36.150
Honey, he's wearing a costume.
He's going as lame.

08:37.049 --> 08:39.325
That's a pretty
good costume, actually.

08:39.385 --> 08:42.491
But I think the Batman costume is way better.
You should go wear that.

08:42.554 --> 08:44.364
Yeah, I don't think
I'm gonna put on a costume,

08:44.423 --> 08:48.565
because I'm not really attending
this party that's at my house.

08:48.628 --> 08:51.507
Hey, listen, if you're mad about
something you should just...

08:51.564 --> 08:53.510
No. I'm not.
I'm not mad.

08:53.566 --> 08:55.136
Really? Listen,
I feel like you are mad.

08:55.201 --> 08:58.341
So maybe you should
just talk to us about it.

08:58.404 --> 09:03.353
My name's Ben. I'm mad.

09:03.409 --> 09:05.047
All right. That was great.
Thank you. So soft.

09:05.111 --> 09:06.181
Soft lips
Thanks for that.

09:06.245 --> 09:08.521
Your fingers are salty.
I'm going to finish my work.

09:08.581 --> 09:11.562
Orin, no! No! Stay out!

09:11.617 --> 09:13.619
Pawnee has suffered
through a tough economy

09:13.686 --> 09:17.828
and what has kept our town alive
is you, the small businessman.

09:17.890 --> 09:19.995
And I'm not referring
to your stature, Gary.

09:20.059 --> 09:22.437
You are a giant
in this community.

09:22.495 --> 09:24.702
So many businesses
represented here today.

09:24.764 --> 09:27.210
Food and Stuff, J.J.'s Diner,

09:27.266 --> 09:31.510
Glennmore Discount Cemetery,
Tramp Stamp Tattoos,

09:31.571 --> 09:35.576
Enormous Kenny's Fried Dough
Stand and Mobile Phone Emporium.

09:35.641 --> 09:37.552
Who else? Sue's Salads.

09:37.610 --> 09:38.680
Ooh!

09:38.744 --> 09:42.658
Smooth Operator Bikini Waxes,
Geoff's Savings and Loan...

09:42.715 --> 09:45.195
And Entertainment 720.

09:45.251 --> 09:47.731
Thank you so much for that
amazing intro, Leslie.

09:47.787 --> 09:49.733
Hi, folks.
My name is Tom Haverford,

09:49.789 --> 09:51.427
and I am here to
tell you a little bit

09:51.490 --> 09:53.470
about Pawnee's
premiere entertainment

09:53.526 --> 09:55.199
<i>and mufti-media
conglomerate...</i>

09:55.261 --> 10:00.677
Entertainment 720 Where
dreams come, they come true

10:01.801 --> 10:03.872
How about we watch
this brief promotional film?

10:03.936 --> 10:05.313
What?

10:06.172 --> 10:09.517
Entertainment 720 has been a fixture
of this community since June.

10:09.575 --> 10:13.785
Tom, listen to me. Turn that off
or give me the remote right now.

10:13.846 --> 10:15.553
It's short. Can you
let it play, please?

10:15.615 --> 10:17.060
You're lucky that
Martin Kernston is here,

10:17.116 --> 10:18.561
'cause you're gonna
need another nipple.

10:18.618 --> 10:19.926
Why?

10:49.382 --> 10:52.226
There. I think I got it.
Yep, you got it.

10:54.320 --> 10:56.391
Can you at least
tell me what you're doing?

10:56.455 --> 11:00.267
I'm a homeowner. I would like
to actually learn something.

11:01.360 --> 11:05.570
Yeah, I'm tightening the valve
stem into the valve shank.

11:05.631 --> 11:09.238
I'm replacing the handle, and
then tightening the set screw,

11:09.301 --> 11:11.975
which will hold it
in place. Now...

11:12.571 --> 11:14.744
Oh, my God. We made it work.

11:14.807 --> 11:18.983
It's a good feeling. Sense
of accomplishment and pride.

11:19.045 --> 11:21.616
Damn it,
I just love it so much.

11:24.116 --> 11:26.153
Are you okay?
Great.

11:26.218 --> 11:27.663
I'm going to go
around this house

11:27.720 --> 11:30.326
and fix everything I can
find that needs fixing.

11:30.389 --> 11:33.199
You want to help?
I really do.

11:33.259 --> 11:35.762
Good. That's next.

11:37.363 --> 11:40.173
I can't reveal my identity because
of various corporate enemies.

11:40.232 --> 11:44.408
<i>But suffice it to say I run</i> a <i>fairly
popular social networking site</i>

11:44.470 --> 11:46.609
And let's face it,

11:46.672 --> 11:50.176
booking E 720 was the smartest
decision I ever made.

11:50.242 --> 11:52.950
<i>I hope you liked this story.</i>

11:54.113 --> 11:55.888
I invented Facebook.

11:55.948 --> 11:57.393
Wow. Okay. Um...

11:58.217 --> 12:01.630
I know that video seemed like
the rantings of a lunatic

12:01.687 --> 12:03.462
pretending to be
Mark Zuckerberg.

12:03.522 --> 12:05.160
That's who that was?
No.

12:05.224 --> 12:06.567
That is impressive.

12:06.625 --> 12:08.434
We're not gonna waste
any more of your time.

12:08.494 --> 12:09.996
Agreed.
Let's get right to it.

12:10.062 --> 12:13.009
Please welcome the
E 720 Mailing List Divas!

12:15.201 --> 12:19.411
I want all y'all to write down
the name and direct phone line

12:19.472 --> 12:21.975
for whoever is in charge of
hiring independent contractors

12:22.041 --> 12:23.918
for your business!

12:23.976 --> 12:27.355
Now, come join me and
let's all take a dip in

12:27.413 --> 12:30.292
the E 720 Mobile Hot Tub!

12:30.382 --> 12:33.556
It's parked right outside.
Let's go!

12:38.491 --> 12:39.799
Hey, Ben.
Hey.

12:39.859 --> 12:40.894
I thought you weren't
coming to the party.

12:40.960 --> 12:43.304
Well, I'm just
having a Butterfinger.

12:43.362 --> 12:45.103
Oh, really?
Is that okay?

12:45.531 --> 12:48.876
No. If you're not part of the
party, you can't have the candy.

12:48.934 --> 12:50.140
Back up.
All right.

12:50.202 --> 12:51.203
Back up.
Okay.

12:51.270 --> 12:55.309
I have one sister.
We steal each other's stuff,

12:55.374 --> 12:57.012
